1 unle ss the guidance document contains sensitive or confidential
2 information not legal to disclose due to privacy laws.
3 C. 1. The State Department of Education shall create the
4 designated Internet website for publication described in subsection
5 B of this section no later than ninety (90) days after the effective
6 date of this act.
7 2. The State Department of Education shall include hyperlinks
8 on the Internet website, in a conspicuous manner, that provide
9 access to the guidance documents received pursuant to subsection B
10 of this section.
11 D. If a guidance document is rescinded by the United States
12 Department of Education, the State Department of Education shall
13 maintain the rescinded guidance document at the location described
14 in subsection C of this section and indicate within fifteen (15)
15 days of such rescission:
16 1. That the document has been rescinded; and
17 2. The date the document was rescinded.
18 E. For purposes of this section, "guidance document" means a
19 federal agency statement of general applicability, other than a rule
20 that has the force and effect of law promulgated in accordance with
21 the notice and comment procedures under 5 U.S.C., Section 553, that
22 is designated by an agency official as setting forth a policy or
23 interpretation on a statutory, regulatory, or technical issue. A
24 guidance document may include, but is not limited to, a memorandum,
